   <text:p text:style-name="P3"><text:span text:style-name="T1">­</text:span><office:annotation office:name="__Annotation__511_3572362212" loext:resolved="false">
     <dc:creator>Vladimir Herdman</dc:creator>
     <dc:date>2026-05-15T20:49:22.083476000</dc:date>
     <meta:creator-initials>VTH</meta:creator-initials>
     <text:p text:style-name="Comment">Current idea is to make it like a love letter/goodbye letter/collection of poems/like a last date.</text:p>
     <text:p text:style-name="Comment"/>
     <text:p text:style-name="Comment">For the cover page, make it like “Goodbye Ollie” and then below it “A collection of Maybe-Poems by Vladimir Tomasovitch Herdman”</text:p>
     <text:p text:style-name="Comment"/>
    </office:annotation>GOODBYE OLLIE<text:span text:style-name="T1">­</text:span><office:annotation-end office:name="__Annotation__511_3572362212"/></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P4"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P4"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P6"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P6"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P7"><office:annotation office:name="__Annotation__701_3423584298" loext:resolved="false">
     <dc:creator>Vladimir Herdman</dc:creator>
     <dc:date>2026-06-01T23:03:00.084500000</dc:date>
     <meta:creator-initials>VTH</meta:creator-initials>
     <text:p text:style-name="Comment">Find out where the “for …” page goes to, and put “for ollie” or something.</text:p>
    </office:annotation>GOODBYE OLLIE<office:annotation-end office:name="__Annotation__701_3423584298"/></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P8"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P8"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P9">Maybe-Poems by</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P10"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P8">Vladimir Tomasovitch Herdman</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P12"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P13"><text:span text:style-name="T2">Copyright </text:span>© 2026<text:span text:style-name="T2"> Vladimir Tomasovitch Herdman.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14">Some rights reserved.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14">This material is licensed under the Creative Commons “Attribution 4.0 International” (CC BY 4.0). For the license agreement, see https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode, and a summary (not a substitute) at https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/deed.en.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14">You are free to copy, distribute, display, <text:span text:style-name="T3">modify, </text:span>and perform this work <text:span text:style-name="T3">in any form </text:span>as long as you give the original author credit, provide a link to the license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so in any reasonable manner, but not in any way that suggests the licensor endorses you or your use.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14">First published <text:span text:style-name="T4">in </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T2">2026 </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T5">by me (Vladimir Tomasovitch Herdman (Vova))</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14">PRINTED… SOMEWHERE, I THINK. AMAZON WASN’T REALLY ALL THAT CLEAR, BUT THEY’RE PRINTING FACILITIES ARE GENERALLY NEAR TO WHERE YOU BUY THIS MATERIAL, SO GOOD LUCK <text:span text:style-name="T4">FIGURING IT OUT</text:span>. IF I’M NOT WRONG, IT SHOULD SAY SOMEWHERE <text:span text:style-name="T4">ON THIS BOOK WHERE</text:span> WAS PRINTED. THOUGH I DON’T REALLY MIND <text:span text:style-name="T4">WHERE</text:span>, AS THIS WAS FREE FROM MY END, <text:span text:style-name="T4">THIS WAS FOR WHOM IT MAY CONCERN</text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P14"/>
